{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"043ec9ba-c63e-4e99-9086-df270959c0e5","content":"Here's what to update:\n\n**1. `*.csproj`** — Change the target framework:\n```xml\n<TargetFramework>net11.0</TargetFramework>\n```\n\n**2. `global.json`** — Pin the new SDK:\n```json\n{ \"sdk\": { \"version\": \"11.0.100\" } }\n```\n\n**3. `Dockerfile`** — Update base images:\n```dockerfile\nFROM mcr.microsoft.com/dotnet/aspnet:11.0 AS base\nFROM mcr.microsoft.com/dotnet/sdk:11.0 AS build\n```\n\n**4. Install the SDK** — Download .NET 11 SDK from https://dotnet.microsoft.com/download/dotnet/11.0.\n\n**5. Check for breaking changes** — Review the [.NET 11 migration guide](https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/dotnet/core/compatibility/11.0) and update any deprecated APIs or NuGet packages (e.g., `Microsoft.AspNetCore.*`, `Microsoft.EntityFrameworkCore.*`) to their 11.x versions.\n\nAfter updating, run `dotnet build && dotnet test` to verify everything compiles and passes.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"10b957e0-355e-4e10-912f-2254c38e0df4","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking how to update their .NET project from .NET 10 to .NET 11. This is a straightforward question I can answer from knowledge — no codebase to explore.","outputTokens":348,"requestId":"6822:2FA099:26C5326:2AB84E3:69FD29E8"},"id":"a8d294ca-ec8c-429a-91d0-0b4f2566fa8a","timestamp":"2026-05-08T00:10:23.897Z","parentId":"929a4d5b-e145-44eb-817c-ff211a642e38"}
